==English==
===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
Coined by a DJ, Gus Gossert, in the 1970s referring to (mostly) white rock & roll groups of the late 1950s and early 1960s.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
#A style of [[vocal]]-based [[rhythm]] and [[blues]] [[music]] popular in the mid-1950s to the early 1960s in America.